    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-26T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-26T21:00:00-05:00" n="780"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d780">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/9: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-26T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 26, 1931—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>81. Organization of new government conforms with article No. 66 of the Chilean
                    Constitution. President of Senate as Vice and Acting President of Chile is
                    forming a cabinet with Montero as chief. Technically Ibañez has asked for
                    permission to leave the country instead of resigning in order to avoid the
                    constitutional obligation to call elections with [<hi rend="italic"
                    >within?</hi>] 60 days.</p>
                <p>National Savings Bank in failing condition and other banks including Central Bank
                    threatened with serious runs. Closing of banks for four days has been
                    authorized. During this time new government hopes to remedy situation by
                    inviting from their foreign correspondents a loan to Central Bank of about 21
                    million dollars and to give as collateral the nitrate bonds of next year. If
                    such a solution proves impossible the issue of paper money will receive serious
                    consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
